entries.meaning: (computing) The operation of destroying older data by recording new data over it.

verbs.description: overwrite (third-person singular simple present overwrites, present participle overwriting, simple past overwrote, past participle overwritten)

entries.meaning: (transitive, computing) To destroy (older) data by recording new data over it.
examples: I accidentally saved my unwanted changes and overwrote the version of the document I wanted to keep.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cover in writing; to write over the top of.

examples: Many trainees consider that by increasing the length of the piece they will construct a good feature. This is often not the case and overwriting can lead to vague and muddled features that confuse the reader and ultimately lose their interest.

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To write in an unnecessarily complicated or florid way; to produce purple prose.
examples: That said, the passage just looked at anticipates rather than participates in greatness. It is too adjectival, a stylistic flaw which suggests an insistence more apparent in the ensuing lines (182-91), where one is torn between thinking that  Shelley is overwriting and that he is staying close to a feverish intensity.
